docs.summary:
The Hamburger Menu is a hidden navigational menu designed to conserve space on your site. 
It is represented by three parallel lines or an icon in the corner of a site and implies
user interaction will trigger an event. When the user clicks the icon, a container expands to reveal 
the hidden menu. The Hamburger Menu container is typically a vertical list of links that navigate the user 
to sections on your site, which is placed over a full screen overlay. The container includes a close button to 
collapse the menu back to its hidden state.
